parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the trailer brakes to become inoperable, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Warning message on the dash indicating a problem with the trailer brakes or wiring system
trailer brakes becoming inoperable
intermittent loss of trailer brake function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while in motion, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.

loss of power
warning lights illuminating on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.

brake pedal sticking to the floor
loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.

burning smell
alternator catching on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leak into the cabin can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system and lead to mold and mildew accumulation.

wet carpet
musty smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels hard to turn
the steering wheel locks or sticks

the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the steering wheel makes a rattling or clattering noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Steering Column Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and steering column can cause the steering wheel to disconnect from the front wheels, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch and key come out of the steering column while driving
the steering wheel makes a rattling or clattering noise
the power steering assist is lost
the vehicle is difficult to steer.
